In this Exercise, you will demonstrate your practical skills in Object-Oriented Programming (OOP). 
You will be required to implement code solutions that apply various OOP concepts. Read each task 
carefully and provide your code solution accordingly. 

Task 1: Shape Hierarchy 
• Create a class called "Shape" with the following properties and methods: 
o Properties: 
▪  Color (string): Represents the color of the shape.  
o Methods: 
o CalculateArea(): Calculates and returns the area of the shape (abstract method). 
o PrintDetails(): Displays the color and area of the shape. 
• Create two derived classes from the Shape class: "Rectangle" and "Circle". 
o Implement the CalculateArea() method in each derived class to calculate the area of 
the corresponding shape. 
o Implement the PrintDetails() method in each derived class to display the color, shape 
type, and area. 

Task 2: Employee Hierarchy 
• Create a base class called "Employee" with the following properties and methods: 
o Properties: 
▪ Name (string): Represents the name of the employee. 
▪ Salary (decimal): Represents the salary of the employee. 
o Methods: 
▪ CalculateBonus(): Calculates and returns the bonus amount for the 
employee (abstract method). 
▪ PrintDetails(): Displays the name, salary, and bonus amount of the 
employee. 
o Create two derived classes from the Employee class: "Manager" and "Developer". 
o Implement the CalculateBonus() method in each derived class to calculate the bonus  
amount based on their specific rules. Give similar for manager just change the 
developer to manager. 
o Implement the PrintDetails() method in each derived class to display the name, 
position, salary, and bonus amount. 

Task 3: Banking System 
• Create a class called "BankAccount" with the following properties and methods: 
o Properties: 
▪ AccountNumber (string): Represents the account number. 
▪ Balance (decimal): Represents the account balance. 
o Methods: 
▪ Deposit(amount): Deposits the specified amount into the account. 
▪ Withdraw(amount): Withdraws the specified amount from the account. 
• Create a derived class called "SavingsAccount" from the BankAccount class. 
o Implement the Withdraw() method in the SavingsAccount class to restrict 
withdrawals if the account balance falls below a certain minimum balance. 
• Create a derived class called "CheckingAccount" from the BankAccount class. 
o Implement the Withdraw() method in the CheckingAccount class to allow  
withdrawals without any restrictions. 
• Note: You can choose appropriate data types and logic for the methods as per your 
understanding. 

Submission Guidelines: 
Submit your complete C# code files (.cs) for the Shape, Rectangle, Circle, Employee, Manager, 
Developer, BankAccount, SavingsAccount, and CheckingAccount classes. 
Evaluation Criteria: 
You will be evaluated based on the correctness and functionality of your code implementation, 
adherence to OOP principles, and the organization and readability of your code. 
